ts connect with us core values  heritage our story meet our founders stories of excellence corporate social responsibility responsible business environment performance voice of marriott our communities new diversity corporate global regions hotel development brands regions why marriott owner and franchisee qualifications contact us investors analyst coverage annual meeting corporate governance corporate overview financial information news sr director product  service innovation job  marriott international inc bethesda md  hospitality online search  current hospitality jobs what where sr director product  service innovation posted july   marriott international inc bethesda md apply share email facebook tweet linkedin about this job description marriott international is the world’s largest hotel company with more brands more hotels and more opportunities for associates to grow and succeed we believe a great career is a journey of discovery and exploration so we ask where will your journey take you requirements job summary the mission of the cx innovation team is to deliver innovations that ensure our enterprise and brands are differentiated relevant and competitive we lead by discovering insights developing concepts and developing prototypes for major initiatives and high profile projects we collaborate with internal and external partners and monitor inmarket performance of new initiatives to ensure the successful build and deployment of breakthrough concepts we are a part of the customer experience discipline that focuses on driving customercentricity throughout marriott the senior director product and service innovation serves as a key leader within the cx innovation team focused on applying and evolving innovation strategies which connect service the hotel environment and the digital ultimately enabling connected and compelling consumer experiences at the property portfolio and enterprise levels this position will lead diverse projects with portfolio and enterprise impact closely collaborating with the vp product  service innovation and vp digital innovation as well as crossdisciplinary leaders and teams within and beyond bmsc ensuring brand operational and digital experience integrity for both on and above property experiences this role will also contribute to the design and adoption of new processes tools and strategies which contribute to the broader mission of the cx team as a cuttingedge coe for innovation style and experience design excellence a key focus area will be elevating enterprise efforts to foster a culture of innovation across teams disciplines and continents a shared charge across leadership as a project leader the role requires the ability to understand the diverse needs of stakeholders across the business apply a deep understanding of consumer market and consumer trends coordinate team members while shepherding the innovation process from insights to concepts and prototypes addressing operational and digital dimensions while pushing for disruptive new thinking and solutions which stretch our brands disciplines and company this position develops strategy for key brand projects synthesize the results of detailed research efforts across a variety of platforms creates unique operational concepts that reflect market and consumer preference and provides an innovation lens to marketbased initiatives across the marriott international enterprise this position plays a key role in high priority project coordination long range strategic planning of portfolio wide initiatives as well as ‘end to end’ concept design and activation this role will have handson involvement for concept activation in high priority hotels and reflects marriott international’s emphasis on and commitment to design leadership operations integration and results of high integrity candidate profile education and experience babfamba or advanced degree preferredworld class experience in two or more of the following  innovation hotel operations productservice design digital design years of professional experience demonstrating progressive career growth and a pattern of exceptional performance in innovation design creative branding hotel operations or business strategy required strong leadership skills that inspire team confidence and respectproficiency in humancentered design process design thinkingexcellent personnel management skills with the ability to nurture the development of both creative and analytical peopleproven ability to build and foster relationshipsexcellent team player with the ability to collaborate effectively with partners project managers art directorsexperience interpreting trends and research to design and implement innovative products and services that support brand visionsolid ability to manage multiple stakeholders and influence the direction of product design  developmentability to problemsolve and leverage resources to optimize department capabilitiespossess knowledge of cutting edge design solutions with an ability to pull inspiration from a variety of input streamsability to present to internal and external audiences as well as listen openly to feedback with the end result of achieving the best work assesses consumer insights brand positioning and market challenges sees the points of differentiation and weaves a clear concise direction that becomes the basis for inspiring the creative product strong analytical skills and experienceability to work on crossfunctional team technical  creative skills experience within a brand organization or design agency creating transactional products in a consumerfacing market preferably with experience working on projects for the hospitality industry effective project management skills with an ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously develop accurate cost estimates and manage to a budgetmust possess knowledge and practice of core principals in brand strategy ops strategy concept and digital designcreative visualization and exceptional art and design skills particularly in regard to creating work with a comprehensive consistent and imaginative look and feel an inborn eye for continuity and qualityability to solve problems and think creativelyability to benchmark other business and design organizations to identify effective technologies processes and design innovationsstrong presentation and communication skillsability to effectively help team members balance user needs with business and technology objectivesstrong design and art direction capability proficient in the latest versions ofadobe products indesign photoshop etc mac osx power point core work activities leads the application and assists in the regular evolution of cx innovation strategies to multibrand portfolio projects and enterprise initiatives with a focus on digital  physical experience design integration and activation leads the synthesis of various research work streams into targeted concepts and prototypes grounded in consumer and operational insights coordinate the concepting and design of new products or services both digital and physical and poc these concepts in market requires the ability to work with large extended teams in a highly matrixed organization manages and integrates large andor multiple disciplines and departments processes andor projects within a discipline generally influences work of crossfunctional or extended teams across bmsc effective stakeholder management is criticalpromotes continual creative improvement and actively contribute to a culture of innovation and excellence in style and design both physical and digitalconceives and creates experienceoriented design solutions that fulfill strategic business objectives balancing needs for consumer relevance and business returndirects all phases of creative work from concept to implementationresponsible for mentoring and leading junior creative staff through critique of their work to maintain consistent creative qualityensures the discipline establishes communicates and drives continent discipline and brand alignment with cx strategyparticipates in many new business development efforts leading creative direction for portfolio projectseffectively translates branding and marketing strategies for a wide range of internal clients into exceptional creative concepts builds strong relationships with cross functional partners in brand management ecommerce marketing to ensure alignment of efforts and prioritiesresearches best practices and new design trends to ensure designs are innovative and cuttingedgeleads and participates in informal and formal brainstorming sessions to drive successful design direction and maintain a consistent level of quality of workrecruits supervises and art directs freelance talent ensure full understanding of client deliverables as well as timely and accurate completion of projectsleads concept development and brainstorming applying innovative thinking and creative ideas to generate design solutions across multiple platformsdevelops creative ideas based on criteria in creative brief andor direction from senior leadershipclient collaborating with team members and copywritersdevelops style of the presentation for existing conceptsdirections determine best format to execute ideaspresents design concepts to clients articulates creative concepts and rationale to clients and other team membersparticipates and leads meetings discussions and presentations as part of the development process for rough concepts to final designrepresents and champions the interests of cx – identify issues voice concern to raise awareness and offer solutions that can be elevated to senior management to addressoversees consultants and agencies on the development of creative projects management competencies leadership communication  conveys information and ideas to others in a convincing and engaging manner through a variety of methods leading through vision and values  keeps the organizations vision and values at the forefront of employee decision making and action managing change  initiates andor manages the change process and energizes it on an ongoing basis taking steps to remove barriers or accelerate its pace serves as role model for how to handle change by maintaining composure and performance level under pressure or when experiencing challenges problem solving and decision making  identifies and understands issues problems and opportunities obtains and compares information from different sources to draw conclusions develops and evaluates alternatives and solutions solves problems and chooses a course of action professional demeanor  exhibits behavioral styles that convey confidence and command respect from others makes a good first impression and represents the company in alignment with its values strategy development  develops business plans by exploring and systematically evaluating opportunities with the greatest potential for producing positive results ensures successful preparation and execution of business plans through effective planning organizing and ongoing evaluation processes managing execution building a successful team  uses an effective interpersonal style to build a cohesive team inspires and sustains team cohesion and engagement by focusing the team on its mission and importance to the organization strategy execution – ensures successful execution across of business plans designed to maximize customer satisfaction profitability and market share through effective planning organizing and ongoing evaluation processes driving for results  sets high standards of performance for self andor others assumes responsibility for work objectives initiates focuses and monitors the efforts of self andor others toward the accomplishment goals proactively takes action and goes beyond what is required building relationships customer relationships  develops and sustains relationships based on an understanding of customerstakeholder needs and actions consistent with the company’s service standards global mindset  supports employees and business partners with diverse styles abilities motivations andor cultural perspectives utilizes differences to drive innovation engagement and enhance business results and ensures employees are given the opportunity to contribute to their full potential strategic partnerships  develops collaborative relationships with fellow employees and business partners by making them feel valued appreciated and included explores partnership opportunities with other people in and outside the organization influences and leverages corporate and continental shared services andor discipline leaders eg hr sales  marketing finance revenue management to achieve objectives maintains effective external relations with government business and industry in respective countries performs effectively as a liaison between locations disciplines and corporate to ensure needed resources are received and corporate strategies are understood and executed generating talent and organizational capability developing others  supports the development of other’s skills and capabilities so that they can fulfill current or future jobrole responsibilities more effectively organizational capability  evaluates and adapts the structure of assignments and work processes to best fit the needs andor support the goals of an organizational unit learning and applying professional expertise continuous learning  actively identifies new areas for learning regularly creates and takes advantage of learning opportunities uses newly gained knowledge and skill on the job and learns through their application technical acumen – expertly understands and utilizes professional skills and knowledge in a specific functional area to conduct and manage everyday business operations generate innovative solutions to approach functionspecific work challenges and function as a thought leader in his or her area of expertise demonstrates working knowledge of disciplinespecific systems tools and business practices – notably market research crosscultural survey and focus group research techniques advanced research methods such as conjoint analysis and the ability to define requirements for effective reporting systems business acumen  understands and utilizes business information to manage everyday operations and generate innovative solutions to approach business and administrative challenges marriott international is an equal opportunity employer committed to hiring a diverse workforce and sustaining an inclusive culture marriott international does not discriminate on the basis of disability veteran status or any other basis protected under federal state or local laws apply share email facebook tweet linkedin about this employer marriott international inc  fernwood road bethesda md  telephone   website wwwmarriottcom corporate office wwwmarriottcom follow us twitter our associates are the heart of our businessat marriott we know our guests will feel at home when we feel at home we deliver our spirit of hospitality each and every day in an environment of teamwork and collaboration explore the possibilitiesso much more than a jobdiscover the benefits of belonging to our global family it’s why so many of our associates come for a job but stay for a career—because this is a place where you can feel at home and it’s why so many associates refer friends and family members for marriott jobs—because here each of us can truly be ourselvescore values  heritagesuccess is never finalour core values make us who we are as we change and grow the beliefs that are most important to us stay the same—putting people first pursuing excellence embracing change acting with integrity and serving our world being part of marriott international means being part of a proud history and a thriving culturewe put people firsttake care of associates and they will take care of the customersthis is our founder’s philosophy and it has made marriott international a great place to work for more than  yea